The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 CAB seeks Imrans help

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Former Pakistan captain Imran Khan will be in the city sometime in January to impart training to the different age-group players of the state as part of CABs three-point programme to develop the game. We have requested Imran for a 3-4 days stint here for our boys, CAB president Jagmohan Dalmiya said . 

CAB has decided to impart training to coaches, players and the support staff from now till the middle of the domestic season. 

As part of training the support staff, former Team India physio Andrew Leipus will be conducting a five-day course from Monday. John Buchanan will also be here to train the coaches in early 2007. 

Meanwhile, after Arun Lals pep-talk for the Ranji players, Ashok Malhotra will conduct motivation classes for the under-22 players shortly. 




